videos.headline: J. Tatum gets the steal and the dunk

videos.description: The top recruit in the nation, Duke forward Harry Giles, takes the court in the first half against Tennessee State for the first time this season.
videos.headline: Harry Giles takes the court for first time with Duke in win
T. McCall with some nice moves and gets the layup to go

videos.description: Tennessee State head coach Dana Ford hopes his team can play better offense in the 2nd half
videos.headline: Tennessee State head coach Dana Ford hopes his team can play better offense in the 2nd half

videos.description: With the game tied early in the second half, Duke's Jasyon Tatum passes to Grayson Allen, who knocks down a 3-pointer to give the Blue Devils the lead over Tennessee State.
videos.headline: Allen swishes a transition 3

videos.description: Duke's Luke Kennard speaks with Jeff Goodman about the Blue Devils' 65-55 win over Tennessee State and the work he's put in that has allowed the game to slow down for him.
videos.headline: Kennard breaks down Duke's slow start against Tennessee State

videos.description: No. 5 Duke closes the first half on a 13-4 run and gets 24 points from Luke Kennard in a 65-55 win over Tennessee State.
videos.headline: Duke overcomes rough start to top Tennessee State
